		<name type="primary" sortindex="1" value="Colo Colo 100 Años" />
		<description>Colo-Colo 100 A&amp;ntilde;os celebrates the centenary of the most popular
			Chilean football club. Players immerse themselves in the rich history of the "Cacique,"
			revisiting legendary players, historic goals, and championship titles from the club's
			founding in 1925 to the present day.

			The core gameplay challenges players to reconstruct the club's timeline. On their turn,
			a player selects a historical event card from their hand and places it into the growing
			timeline on the table based on when they believe the event occurred. Once placed, the
			card is flipped to reveal the date. If the chronological order is correct, the card
			remains; if incorrect, the player receives a Yellow Card. Accumulating two Yellow Cards
			results in a Red Card and expulsion from the game.

			To add the tension of a real match, the deck includes "Wild Cards" with football-themed
			actions such as "VAR Review," "Penalty," or "Offside." These special cards allow players
			to annul opponents' moves, force them to play extra cards, or avoid penalties. The
			winner is the last player remaining in the game.

			&amp;mdash;description from the publisher</description>
